WEBVTT

00:20.270 --> 00:23.356
How have you been, Eun-ho?

00:25.442 --> 00:29.279
After graduating, I started a company
with my college friends.

00:32.615 --> 00:34.284
Do you still do kumdo?

00:36.161 --> 00:37.912
I quit after getting crushed by you.

00:41.291 --> 00:42.876
I should've gone easy on you.

00:52.844 --> 00:54.763
I struggled a lot after you dropped out.

00:56.598 --> 00:57.432
Dropped out?

00:58.600 --> 00:59.559
What happened?

01:02.103 --> 01:03.688
So that's the backstory, huh?

01:04.189 --> 01:05.023
Well…

01:09.110 --> 01:10.779
I had my reasons.

01:12.989 --> 01:14.657
You could've at least kept in touch.

01:15.867 --> 01:16.701
I'm sorry.

01:20.413 --> 01:22.207
So? What have you been up to?

01:24.209 --> 01:27.045
I'm a webtoon producer.

01:29.839 --> 01:30.757
WEBTOON PD

01:31.341 --> 01:32.342
A business card?

01:33.718 --> 01:36.387
I work at a company called Naemo,
near Hapjeong.

01:37.680 --> 01:38.681
That's so cool.

01:40.016 --> 01:40.892
It suits you.

01:42.352 --> 01:43.937
Here's my card.

01:48.066 --> 01:50.485
Producer Seo Mi-rae.

01:51.945 --> 01:52.946
For the first time,

01:53.029 --> 01:55.949
I'm the same person here
as I am in reality.

01:58.952 --> 02:02.747
It feels weird to hear you call me that.

02:20.807 --> 02:21.641
We're here.

02:21.724 --> 02:22.892
This is the place.

02:25.228 --> 02:27.021
So this is your company.

02:31.776 --> 02:33.319
Let's meet more often from now on.

02:35.113 --> 02:35.947
Okay.

02:36.030 --> 02:37.866
I can take you home. Where do you live?

02:38.366 --> 02:40.618
It's okay. You must be busy, so get going.

02:41.619 --> 02:42.453
It's dark out.

02:43.496 --> 02:47.208
I'm not 20 anymore.
I even drink soju at a pocha by myself.

02:48.835 --> 02:51.379
Even in college,
you never drank like most 20-year-olds.

02:55.175 --> 02:56.634
Anyway, I'll get going.

02:57.135 --> 02:57.969
See you soon.

03:43.640 --> 03:44.641
Hello?

03:45.141 --> 03:46.100
Hello?

03:47.227 --> 03:48.228
Hello?

03:48.728 --> 03:49.854
Did you make it home?

03:50.355 --> 03:52.565
I wanted to make sure you got back safely.

03:54.901 --> 03:55.860
Eun-ho?

03:56.444 --> 03:58.446
What is this? How is he calling me?

03:58.947 --> 03:59.781
Hello?

03:59.864 --> 04:02.367
Oh, yes. Just a moment.

04:09.040 --> 04:11.209
All subscribers
with a basic plan and above

04:11.292 --> 04:16.089
can send and receive calls and messages
with the characters after logging out.

04:16.172 --> 04:17.298
That's crazy!

04:17.382 --> 04:19.676
Hello? Isn't this Seo Mi-rae's phone?

04:20.426 --> 04:21.928
Oh, yes, Eun-ho.

04:22.011 --> 04:24.806
What are you up to?
I'm having trouble falling asleep.

04:25.890 --> 04:27.684
I'm also wide awake now.

04:28.184 --> 04:31.020
Then shall we talk until you get sleepy?

04:31.771 --> 04:32.730
Shall we?

04:34.857 --> 04:36.651
I've never met anyone who knows it.

04:36.734 --> 04:38.611
Any horror fan would know that film.

04:38.695 --> 04:40.989
The protagonist, being a villager,
was a fun choice.

04:41.072 --> 04:41.906
Right?

04:41.990 --> 04:46.369
Most folk horror films would go with
an outsider who's just arrived.

04:46.869 --> 04:47.704
Exactly!

04:48.371 --> 04:51.165
Want to watch a movie together next time?

04:52.333 --> 04:53.584
-A movie?
-Yeah.

04:53.668 --> 04:56.921
Let's meet near your office.
I'll come to Hapjeong Station.

04:57.005 --> 04:57.839
What?

04:58.965 --> 05:00.550
Are you uncomfortable with that?

05:03.011 --> 05:04.178
No, that's not…

05:11.311 --> 05:15.815
If you're okay with it, I can head over
around the time you get off work tomorrow.

05:26.743 --> 05:28.661
The realism is breathtaking.

05:29.245 --> 05:30.288
Sounds good.

05:31.539 --> 05:32.415
Then…

05:33.374 --> 05:34.500
I'll see you tomorrow.

05:40.798 --> 05:46.554
EPISODE 5
THE CAVEATS OF PERFECTION

05:53.603 --> 05:55.271
Sorry I'm late.

05:55.355 --> 05:57.023
Let me go grab some coffee.

05:57.106 --> 05:58.191
I already made some.

05:58.274 --> 06:00.276
It's cold, though, since you're late.

06:01.402 --> 06:02.570
Thank you.

06:03.071 --> 06:06.157
I was reviewing a submitted file
and lost track of time.

06:06.240 --> 06:07.241
Shall we get started?

06:09.035 --> 06:12.538
I didn't like this piece that much.
It was too imitative of existing works.

06:13.289 --> 06:14.374
Me too.

06:14.457 --> 06:16.459
Is anything ever completely original?

06:17.168 --> 06:19.337
The lines and page layouts
are too amateurish.

06:19.420 --> 06:21.339
Which can be fixed with our help.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.592
Do you think you can also fix
such a childish plot?

06:24.675 --> 06:27.804
Some titles top the charts
despite having a childish plot, you know.

06:34.102 --> 06:34.936
What?

06:35.978 --> 06:37.563
No, I just…

06:38.523 --> 06:40.858
Which titles might you be referring to?

06:40.942 --> 06:42.693
There are plenty of them, as you know.

06:45.029 --> 06:47.115
You're right. There are plenty.

06:49.742 --> 06:51.577
What's his problem today?

06:52.995 --> 06:54.163
Let's take a break.

07:09.762 --> 07:12.765
Did you get to work okay? Good luck today!

07:13.516 --> 07:17.019
When was the last time I received a text
from a guy checking in on me?

07:22.900 --> 07:25.069
Heading out for lunch? Let me come with.

07:25.695 --> 07:28.489
I have a lunch meeting.
Why don't you eat with Kyeong-nam?

07:28.573 --> 07:29.490
Shall we?

07:30.825 --> 07:32.076
We also have plans.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.578
Enjoy your meal.

07:35.872 --> 07:36.706
Let's go.

07:37.206 --> 07:38.040
Sure.

07:59.770 --> 08:01.314
This is so awkward.

08:03.733 --> 08:04.734
Do you like romance?

08:05.818 --> 08:06.652
What?

08:06.736 --> 08:08.863
I'm asking
because we'll be judging together.

08:10.698 --> 08:12.742
No. I don't like it.

08:13.367 --> 08:14.202
Me neither.

08:15.161 --> 08:16.287
So what?

08:18.706 --> 08:19.707
So what do you like?

08:22.210 --> 08:23.169
Horror.

08:23.836 --> 08:24.670
Why is that?

08:26.339 --> 08:28.174
Well, it's just…

08:28.257 --> 08:32.803
I barely notice my heart most of the time,
so I like the way they make it race.

08:33.971 --> 08:35.640
I also like horror. A lot.

08:35.723 --> 08:37.558
Who asked you?

08:40.394 --> 08:42.813
It must be hard for you
to work on The Man to Know.

08:44.023 --> 08:45.733
Yeah, I guess.

08:46.234 --> 08:48.152
I only got assigned that job
thanks to you.

08:49.237 --> 08:50.071
Hang in there.

09:05.920 --> 09:07.838
I'll be there soon.

09:10.007 --> 09:12.260
Take your time, and don't trip.

09:22.728 --> 09:23.563
Eun-ho!

09:28.859 --> 09:30.444
-Am I late?
-No.

09:31.404 --> 09:33.030
The movie is about to start. Let's go.

09:39.453 --> 09:40.746
Don't kill me!

09:46.711 --> 09:48.045
Don't kill me…

09:50.256 --> 09:52.300
Please don't kill me!

09:52.967 --> 09:54.719
Please don't kill me…

10:19.493 --> 10:20.953
Want some popcorn?

10:34.050 --> 10:37.511
What was it they said? That excitement
is not an emotion but a sensation?

10:39.972 --> 10:40.973
It's so sweet.

10:45.478 --> 10:46.646
A bit messy, isn't it?

10:49.273 --> 10:50.691
It's really nice in here.

10:51.192 --> 10:52.610
Everyone is out of the office.

10:53.194 --> 10:55.279
Take a look around. I'll get you a drink.

11:14.215 --> 11:15.383
I miss everyone.

11:21.430 --> 11:23.516
Looking back now, we were really young.

11:25.559 --> 11:26.686
I didn't know back then…

11:31.023 --> 11:32.608
that I'd never…

11:34.610 --> 11:36.028
forget about you.

11:43.536 --> 11:46.205
We have a nice rooftop.
Want to get some fresh air?

11:57.717 --> 11:58.551
What is it?

12:34.587 --> 12:36.088
Are you going to disappear again?

12:41.051 --> 12:41.886
No.

12:47.349 --> 12:49.810
I'm not going anywhere.

13:01.655 --> 13:04.533
On my way to work. Have a nice day.

13:11.373 --> 13:12.875
Anything you want to eat today?

13:14.919 --> 13:16.712
I haven't thought about it yet.

13:16.796 --> 13:20.716
You wanted lasagna last time.
I'll find a place that makes good lasagna.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.676
…I suspect that might be a trace of it.

13:22.760 --> 13:25.471
Like you said, it does have its strengths,

13:25.554 --> 13:28.182
but are they enough
to make up for the shortcomings--

13:28.265 --> 13:29.308
What are you doing?

13:37.024 --> 13:37.858
Why do you ask?

13:40.319 --> 13:41.237
It's nothing.

13:43.405 --> 13:44.532
Please continue.

13:47.326 --> 13:48.285
Eun-ho!

13:52.373 --> 13:53.624
Am I late?

13:53.707 --> 13:54.542
You're pretty.

14:08.430 --> 14:11.767
The few hours of freedom I have
after getting off work.

14:17.189 --> 14:20.109
I've finally found the perfect way

14:20.943 --> 14:22.361
to spend that time.

14:24.989 --> 14:25.865
Look at this one.

14:56.979 --> 15:00.649
Have I ever been on
such a perfect date before?

15:02.234 --> 15:03.819
This is so nice.

15:18.417 --> 15:21.253
Has time ever flown by so fast?

16:24.483 --> 16:25.526
Stop crying, okay?

16:32.241 --> 16:33.075
Hey.

16:34.326 --> 16:37.663
Drink this and forget about it,
or go beg him to take you back.

16:45.504 --> 16:48.215
There's none. They simply don't exist.

16:49.508 --> 16:50.592
What do you mean?

16:51.427 --> 16:54.513
No man in this world
is a perfect match for me.

16:55.055 --> 16:59.893
If I can't find one after meeting 30 guys,
that means no such man exists.

17:01.687 --> 17:03.605
Then what, are you gonna stop dating?

17:03.689 --> 17:05.941
I don't know. Fuck!

17:08.902 --> 17:10.738
Why are you suddenly swearing?

17:11.321 --> 17:12.781
It was all a waste!

17:12.865 --> 17:15.034
If I had put all that time
into something else,

17:15.117 --> 17:18.704
I wouldn't be worn out dealing with kids,
even with a master's degree.

17:18.787 --> 17:20.581
I would've made something of myself!

17:21.707 --> 17:24.793
Hey, don't be so dramatic.
It's not too late.

17:25.294 --> 17:26.795
It's hopeless.

17:27.880 --> 17:30.549
I've had all my energy drained by guys.

17:30.632 --> 17:32.843
Now I don't have the strength
to do anything.

17:34.470 --> 17:35.304
Hey.

17:37.806 --> 17:40.559
You have it better than me.

17:41.310 --> 17:42.561
I should have

17:43.228 --> 17:46.565
just lived like you!

17:53.739 --> 17:54.573
What?

17:59.495 --> 18:00.537
JI-YEON

18:00.621 --> 18:02.915
Hey, how's my profile picture?

18:02.998 --> 18:04.792
Can you tell I'm pretending to be okay?

18:06.752 --> 18:08.003
So obvious.

18:08.504 --> 18:10.839
EUN-HO

18:11.965 --> 18:12.925
Hello.

18:13.008 --> 18:15.302
Are you on your way?
What's up with your friend?

18:16.095 --> 18:17.805
She broke up with her boyfriend.

18:19.306 --> 18:20.724
That sounds rough.

18:21.308 --> 18:22.392
Hey, Eun-ho.

18:22.476 --> 18:26.146
Do you think there's a perfect match
for us somewhere in this world?

18:26.230 --> 18:28.482
Not sure. Why do you ask?

18:28.982 --> 18:30.442
Just curious.

18:30.526 --> 18:33.987
I guess I'm not good enough for you
if you're asking that.

18:35.280 --> 18:36.406
It's not like that.

18:38.367 --> 18:40.369
The weather's gotten really cold now.

18:41.286 --> 18:45.207
Had I found the answer
that Ji-yeon couldn't?

18:53.590 --> 18:55.008
-Eun-ho.
-Yes?

18:55.509 --> 18:59.263
When you're with me, do you enjoy it?

19:03.058 --> 19:04.977
First the call, and now this.

19:06.103 --> 19:07.729
That's an odd question to ask.

19:07.813 --> 19:10.649
Tell me. Do you really enjoy
being with me?

19:15.070 --> 19:16.321
What are you really asking?

19:22.369 --> 19:23.954
Our relationship…

19:25.956 --> 19:27.332
is a good thing, right?

19:28.333 --> 19:30.169
Is being with you

19:31.044 --> 19:32.629
the right choice for me?

19:36.008 --> 19:36.842
Mi-rae.

19:40.179 --> 19:42.264
When I'm with you, I'm so happy.

19:44.266 --> 19:46.018
And when I'm not with you,

19:47.352 --> 19:49.104
thinking about you makes me happy.

19:53.525 --> 19:55.277
What do you think of?

19:57.196 --> 19:58.238
The way you smile.

19:59.615 --> 20:01.033
The way you walk.

20:01.617 --> 20:02.701
The way you eat.

20:03.535 --> 20:04.953
The way you talk. Everything.

20:07.915 --> 20:08.916
So,

20:09.958 --> 20:11.210
put your doubts aside.

20:14.379 --> 20:15.214
Okay.

20:16.924 --> 20:17.966
I'm hurt, you know.

20:19.676 --> 20:20.510
Sorry.

20:28.477 --> 20:30.145
Ji-yeon couldn't find her answer.

20:33.565 --> 20:35.317
But I think I've found mine.

20:44.701 --> 20:47.287
Why would you eat with us?
Where's your team?

20:48.330 --> 20:51.833
They all wanted to go eat sushi,
and I can't eat uncooked food.

20:53.418 --> 20:56.004
I'm glad you're here.
You are always welcome to join us.

20:58.173 --> 21:00.759
Hey, you're all gonna attend
the workshop, aren't you?

21:01.843 --> 21:03.136
Workshop?

21:03.637 --> 21:05.555
-Yes, it's this week.
-You're not going?

21:06.890 --> 21:08.016
I'm not gonna go.

21:08.517 --> 21:09.518
I don't want to.

21:10.602 --> 21:11.687
Do I have to go?

21:13.605 --> 21:16.942
Don't you remember what happened
two years ago when you didn't go?

21:17.025 --> 21:17.859
Huh?

21:20.362 --> 21:22.155
Come on, it's barbecue time!

21:22.239 --> 21:24.741
-Barbecue!
-Mi-rae, it's barbecue!

21:24.825 --> 21:26.827
-Get in!
-Come on, Mi-rae!

21:36.253 --> 21:37.337
It's packed.

21:39.047 --> 21:39.923
I'm full.

21:41.758 --> 21:45.679
It's too much for one person to take on.
Are you sure she'll be okay?

21:45.762 --> 21:48.932
The authors have said yes,
so we can proceed as scheduled, but--

21:49.016 --> 21:51.393
-Let us know if you need help.
-Then it's settled.

21:51.476 --> 21:53.395
Sir, can you take a look at--

21:53.478 --> 21:54.980
-Anything else to add?
-No.

21:55.063 --> 21:55.897
Meeting adjourned.

21:59.318 --> 22:03.238
Hey, are you eating? Eat your fill.
Pretend that I'm paying for it.

22:05.741 --> 22:08.535
Sir, during the last workshop,
I had a stomach bug--

22:08.618 --> 22:10.454
Dong-min, order one stomach bug for…

22:12.414 --> 22:15.208
Get us one aged rib, man!

22:15.917 --> 22:17.502
Mi-rae, you're still here?

22:18.628 --> 22:19.963
First time seeing you here.

22:20.047 --> 22:23.467
The last workshop was amazing.
Workshops are the reason I haven't quit.

22:23.550 --> 22:25.802
That went on for three weeks.

22:25.886 --> 22:28.180
Hwang Byeong-hak is impossible
when he gets sulky.

22:28.263 --> 22:32.267
He's two years older now, so this time,
I think we're looking at six weeks.

22:34.144 --> 22:36.188
Kyeong-nam,
you didn't go back then either.

22:36.271 --> 22:37.606
Were you okay?

22:37.689 --> 22:39.733
Yes. I was okay.

22:39.816 --> 22:42.027
You're not going, are you?

22:43.070 --> 22:44.446
You're going, aren't you?

22:45.322 --> 22:47.991
Well, it'd be awkward
if I were the only one not going.

22:49.242 --> 22:50.160
I'm going.

22:50.744 --> 22:53.413
You're going to attend a two-day workshop?

22:53.497 --> 22:55.832
What's gotten into you? Are you bored?

22:55.916 --> 22:56.875
No.

22:57.876 --> 23:01.254
My parents live nearby,
and I have to see them on Friday.

23:01.922 --> 23:05.342
But it's a weekend.
You should spend time with your family.

23:06.510 --> 23:07.677
I'll take care of it.

23:09.638 --> 23:11.681
FLAMING JJAMPPONG

23:17.729 --> 23:19.481
That devilish jerk.

23:19.981 --> 23:23.235
Wow, this is the scent of nature.

23:24.069 --> 23:25.862
Wake up! How long are you going to sleep?

23:25.946 --> 23:27.322
WORK ALL NIGHT! WORKSHOP ALL NIGHT!

23:27.406 --> 23:29.658
Hey, you guys aren't carrying much.

23:30.158 --> 23:31.952
Boys, come back down here.

23:32.035 --> 23:35.163
Have fun. I miss you.

23:42.921 --> 23:44.589
Okay. I'll be in touch.

23:55.225 --> 23:56.059
Hello.

23:56.685 --> 23:57.519
Hello.

24:01.648 --> 24:04.401
Eun-ju! Take a picture of me over here.

24:04.901 --> 24:06.445
NAEMO'S 7TH ULTIMATE GEEK CONTEST

24:06.528 --> 24:09.698
All right, this is an old tradition
at our company.

24:09.781 --> 24:11.741
Who's the real deal?
The ultimate geek contest!

24:15.787 --> 24:19.416
The winner will have
the special opportunity to choose

24:19.499 --> 24:24.296
from a variety of collectible items
brought by Director Hwang!

24:24.379 --> 24:26.548
Hey, these are all limited edition!

24:27.132 --> 24:29.259
No improvement at all.

24:29.342 --> 24:31.178
-Since last time?
-We do this every time.

24:31.261 --> 24:33.555
Now then, here's question number one.

24:33.638 --> 24:36.975
Listen to the following line from a comic,
and guess which comic it is.

24:37.058 --> 24:40.979
"I talked to a guy for the first time.
Am I about to get a boyfriend?"

24:43.648 --> 24:45.901
-Seo Mi-rae.
-Mi-rae was faster. The answer is?

24:45.984 --> 24:47.986
I Want to Hold Aono-kun so Badly
I Could Die?

24:48.069 --> 24:50.489
-Correct!
-Really?

24:51.990 --> 24:53.074
Remember the name.

24:53.158 --> 24:55.410
-She's on Team 2.
-Question number two.

24:55.494 --> 24:56.536
Bringing up a classic.

24:56.620 --> 24:58.246
In Dragon Ball,

24:58.330 --> 25:01.500
which World Martial Arts Tournament
did Tenshinhan first appear in?

25:01.583 --> 25:02.584
Hye-bin!

25:03.710 --> 25:04.544
The 37th!

25:04.628 --> 25:05.504
Wrong.

25:05.587 --> 25:07.672
Mi-rae. The 23rd?

25:07.756 --> 25:09.758
-Wrong!
-It's over the 30th.

25:09.841 --> 25:10.842
No, it's not.

25:11.343 --> 25:12.928
-Kyeong-nam.
-Yes?

25:13.011 --> 25:15.722
-The 22nd.
-The 22nd?

25:15.805 --> 25:17.432
Correct!

25:21.186 --> 25:22.020
Kyeong-nam!

25:22.103 --> 25:24.773
In Polar Night, Cha Dong-hwan
served in the air force for--

25:24.856 --> 25:26.650
-Seo Mi-rae!
-Jesus.

25:26.733 --> 25:27.817
-Yes?
-Eight years.

25:27.901 --> 25:29.861
Eight years, correct!

25:30.362 --> 25:32.864
In Villain to Kill,
when Kwon Yu-ri is in danger,

25:32.948 --> 25:34.533
the hotelier helps her and says…

25:34.616 --> 25:36.117
-Park Kyeong-nam.
-Yes?

25:36.201 --> 25:37.202
"Good morning."

25:37.285 --> 25:38.537
Ding ding ding!

25:38.620 --> 25:40.956
In A Bona Fide Killer,
Bona's child carries around--

25:41.039 --> 25:41.915
Kyeong-nam.

25:41.998 --> 25:43.542
-Yes?
-Kongdoli.

25:43.625 --> 25:44.543
Correct!

25:44.626 --> 25:46.211
In Theme Park of Death, Baek Jin--

25:46.294 --> 25:47.546
-Seo Mi-rae!
-Yes?

25:47.629 --> 25:48.630
Rolling Z Train.

25:48.713 --> 25:49.965
Rolling Z Train, correct!

25:50.048 --> 25:51.383
Yup. She got that one right.

25:51.466 --> 25:54.469
In Transfer Student at Apocalypse High,
Geon-u's friend's sister--

25:54.553 --> 25:55.637
Kyeong-nam.

25:55.720 --> 25:57.389
-Class 2-5.
-Correct!

25:57.889 --> 26:00.892
In Abandoned House Diary, how tall
is Oh Seong-chan, who keeps passing out?

26:00.976 --> 26:02.102
Mi-rae.

26:02.185 --> 26:03.270
175 cm?

26:03.853 --> 26:05.063
-Wrong!
-Kyeong-nam.

26:06.731 --> 26:07.899
176.

26:08.650 --> 26:10.151
Correct!

26:12.279 --> 26:13.196
-Mi-rae.
-Kyeong-nam.

26:13.280 --> 26:14.197
-Mi-rae!
-Kyeong-nam.

26:14.281 --> 26:15.782
Seo Mi-rae, Arapra Garatus!

26:15.865 --> 26:18.076
Arapra Garatus, correct!

26:18.159 --> 26:20.078
That's it! Arapra Garatus!

26:21.121 --> 26:23.957
Our very own Seo Mi-rae
got the last question right.

26:24.040 --> 26:26.918
It was a nail-biter,
with both participants evenly matched!

26:27.002 --> 26:29.462
Now, I will be announcing the results.

26:29.546 --> 26:34.551
Naemo's 7th Ultimate Geek Contest 2025.
And the winner is…

26:40.140 --> 26:42.309
Park Kyeong-nam!

26:44.060 --> 26:47.897
Go Team 1! Go Park Kyeong-nam!

26:51.860 --> 26:55.447
Ms. Seo, which prize do you want
to find the most in the treasure hunt?

26:57.907 --> 26:59.075
An early leave.

27:02.329 --> 27:03.204
I'm so cold!

27:03.288 --> 27:05.123
I can't keep looking.

27:05.206 --> 27:08.126
Who even hides treasures in a stream
when it's this cold?

27:08.209 --> 27:09.377
A centipede!

27:10.837 --> 27:12.339
-Where?
-Oh, it's not.

27:12.422 --> 27:13.840
-It's a twig.
-Hey, your phone!

27:13.923 --> 27:15.592
Oh no! It's going down the stream!

27:15.675 --> 27:16.968
Oh God, no!

27:17.052 --> 27:18.219
-What do we do?
-No!

27:18.303 --> 27:20.180
-What do we do?
-No!

27:22.265 --> 27:24.601
Dong-min!

27:34.235 --> 27:35.195
Holy!

27:35.695 --> 27:37.572
-I'll show you.
-Just get in there.

27:37.656 --> 27:39.783
-Hurry! It's over there!
-Hold on a sec.

27:39.866 --> 27:41.743
-Hurry up!
-Go after it!

28:26.037 --> 28:27.122
Thank you.

28:28.456 --> 28:29.290
Aren't you cold?

28:29.874 --> 28:32.460
It must have hit a rock.
The screen's cracked.

28:34.295 --> 28:37.173
You're right. I only just bought this!

28:37.257 --> 28:39.092
I'm going to change my pants.

28:43.138 --> 28:44.723
Well done, Kyeong-nam.

28:47.225 --> 28:49.894
Hey, are you okay?
That was a brand-new phone.

28:49.978 --> 28:52.397
Yes, I'm fine.

28:53.356 --> 28:54.399
I feel good.

28:54.482 --> 28:55.567
-Huh?
-Good.

28:57.986 --> 28:59.362
Okay, let's all drink!

28:59.446 --> 29:02.574
-Hey, any song requests?
-Cheers!

29:03.324 --> 29:05.243
Fine, I'll just take care of it.

29:07.537 --> 29:10.790
I never thought
you would be attending this workshop.

29:10.874 --> 29:14.461
Since your parents live nearby,
do they farm oriental melons?

29:14.544 --> 29:18.047
Park Kyeong-nam definitely has
the makings of a star.

29:20.592 --> 29:22.343
You can't be serious.

29:22.427 --> 29:23.261
You saw him.

29:23.344 --> 29:26.848
He went in without any hesitation
when everyone else was standing around.

29:27.891 --> 29:28.808
Then he just left.

29:29.309 --> 29:31.227
Women go crazy for that kind of thing.

29:31.728 --> 29:32.812
Have a drink.

29:39.944 --> 29:40.862
I'll go get soju.

29:40.945 --> 29:42.447
As I turned into the alleyway

29:42.530 --> 29:44.699
The alleyway

29:45.784 --> 29:50.121
My heart was pounding

29:50.205 --> 29:52.207
Was pounding

29:52.290 --> 29:55.251
Curtains draped

29:55.335 --> 29:57.378
Over your window…

30:03.635 --> 30:04.469
Ms. Seo.

30:05.220 --> 30:06.054
Yes?

30:09.265 --> 30:10.099
What?

30:11.893 --> 30:12.769
Is that water?

30:14.896 --> 30:15.730
This?

30:16.481 --> 30:17.398
It's soju.

30:19.067 --> 30:21.069
Oh, it's soju.

30:22.445 --> 30:23.822
Soju's not good though.

30:24.906 --> 30:25.740
Huh?

30:26.407 --> 30:28.243
Soju is not good.

30:36.292 --> 30:39.754
This is also soju. The water's over there.

30:42.257 --> 30:43.424
Thank you.

30:50.223 --> 30:52.892
Seriously? He's a lightweight?

30:55.770 --> 30:56.604
Hot!

31:20.461 --> 31:22.213
Why don't these match?

31:28.094 --> 31:30.221
The bottles and lids don't match.

31:30.805 --> 31:33.892
What are you, a matchmaker?
Why are you trying to match them?

31:33.975 --> 31:37.520
No, it's this bottle.
It's supposed to have a matching lid.

31:39.647 --> 31:41.065
Hey. Look.

31:42.191 --> 31:43.735
-Over there.
-What in the world?

31:43.818 --> 31:45.945
I mean, there has to be a lid.

31:46.029 --> 31:47.155
Hey, look!

31:47.238 --> 31:48.948
Eun-ju, look at that!

31:49.032 --> 31:51.576
This guy has a weird habit
when he's drunk.

31:52.076 --> 31:53.953
Kyeong-nam. Let's get you to bed.

31:56.039 --> 31:58.374
You don't get it. It needs to have a lid.

31:58.458 --> 32:00.251
Yes, it does. God, you're heavy.

32:00.335 --> 32:03.588
-We're seeing so many new sides of him.
-This is important.

32:03.671 --> 32:05.089
Here. Careful.

32:05.173 --> 32:08.259
Did you hear what I said?
Without a lid, something bad will happen.

32:08.343 --> 32:10.803
-Sure, that's important.
-I'm serious.

32:10.887 --> 32:12.597
Sleep, okay? Sleep.

32:14.015 --> 32:16.935
-Hey, you guys. Sing a song.
-It really needs a lid.

32:17.018 --> 32:18.269
-Sing a song.
-I'm okay.

32:18.353 --> 32:20.271
-Well…
-Don't pick it up.

32:20.772 --> 32:24.859
Sing a song!

32:24.943 --> 32:26.402
Go on. Sing a song now.

32:26.486 --> 32:28.112
-I really can't--
-Do it!

32:28.780 --> 32:33.701
But after a long while

32:34.285 --> 32:38.957
I was crying on my own

32:39.040 --> 32:41.042
Feeling the pain

32:41.125 --> 32:45.630
I once caused you
Would you…

32:48.132 --> 32:49.133
The end.

32:51.427 --> 32:53.429
I didn't know this song was so short.

32:54.222 --> 32:55.431
Kyeong-nam's awake.

32:55.515 --> 32:57.934
Feel better? You can go back to sleep.

32:58.017 --> 32:59.102
I'm good.

32:59.852 --> 33:00.937
My ears were hurting.

33:01.020 --> 33:02.021
Your ears?

33:03.022 --> 33:05.274
-What on earth is he on about?
-His ears?

33:05.358 --> 33:06.609
Hey, your turn.

33:50.111 --> 33:52.572
I told her not to date
someone from the office.

33:56.659 --> 33:59.370
Mi-rae, aren't you glad you came?
Wasn't it so much fun?

33:59.454 --> 34:02.373
Director Hwang,
that was the best workshop of my life.

34:02.874 --> 34:05.376
-Don't skip these from now on.
-Of course I won't.

34:05.460 --> 34:08.254
-Guys, wasn't that fun?
-Let's go in Kyeong-nam's car.

34:09.005 --> 34:10.381
Dong-min!

34:10.465 --> 34:13.342
We'll take the bus.
Please take Eun-ju home safely.

34:13.426 --> 34:14.594
You can go in my car.

34:14.677 --> 34:17.597
Yes! It'll be more comfortable.
He's okay with it.

34:19.182 --> 34:20.349
-Come on!
-What?

34:21.059 --> 34:23.394
-Get in.
-Hurry up!

34:27.648 --> 34:29.317
I think I'll sit in the back.

34:29.400 --> 34:30.234
What?

34:37.200 --> 34:38.034
You getting in?

34:41.496 --> 34:42.663
Yes. Okay.

34:59.597 --> 35:00.932
You can drop me off here.

35:01.015 --> 35:02.934
I'll get out here too.

35:05.394 --> 35:07.063
Whoa, don't throw up in the car.

35:07.647 --> 35:09.982
Get out of the car. Hurry!

35:12.235 --> 35:13.486
I'll get out here too.

35:13.569 --> 35:14.612
You don't live here.

35:14.695 --> 35:16.656
I can take the subway. Thank you.

35:16.739 --> 35:18.908
I'll drive you.
I'm headed that way anyway.

35:24.455 --> 35:26.958
Get home safe. Kyeong-nam, thank you.

35:27.041 --> 35:28.626
See you tomorrow.

35:39.846 --> 35:42.098
Your diffuser has a really nice scent.

35:44.016 --> 35:44.851
Just shut up.

35:44.934 --> 35:47.311
I can smell alcohol on you.
You must've had too much.

35:47.395 --> 35:48.396
What?

35:49.480 --> 35:52.066
I didn't though. Did I?

35:55.319 --> 35:57.405
Can I drop you off near Yongsan Station?

35:57.488 --> 35:58.322
Yes.

35:58.990 --> 36:01.492
But don't you live in Seongsu?

36:01.993 --> 36:02.827
I do.

36:03.619 --> 36:04.453
Then why…

36:04.537 --> 36:06.789
I have a meeting with Hwany there.

36:07.790 --> 36:08.708
On a Sunday?

36:09.500 --> 36:10.334
Yes.

36:12.170 --> 36:14.463
I thought you really cared about
work-life balance.

36:14.547 --> 36:18.009
I don't want to get in the way
while he's trying to step up his game.

36:20.219 --> 36:23.347
He's trying to step up his game?

36:23.431 --> 36:24.640
I see.

36:25.141 --> 36:28.644
How's Ms. Yun doing?
Mr. Hwang seemed worried about her.

36:30.313 --> 36:31.397
Worried about what?

36:31.480 --> 36:34.400
Sales, probably.
They dropped a lot last month, after all.

36:35.651 --> 36:38.905
That was just a temporary dip
due to the coin event and her break.

36:38.988 --> 36:42.658
That, and her title has low ratings,
so I suppose it's making him nervous.

36:44.702 --> 36:45.536
I see.

36:45.620 --> 36:48.623
Having said that, it looks like
Hwany will be doing the short story

36:48.706 --> 36:51.709
that Ms. Yun was supposed to work on,
at the advertiser's request.

36:54.462 --> 36:56.047
Can I drop you off right there?

36:56.631 --> 36:57.465
Yes.

36:58.633 --> 37:03.262
Why does Mr. Hwang keep talking to you
instead of telling me himself?

37:03.888 --> 37:04.722
Who knows?

37:07.850 --> 37:09.268
Thank you for the ride.

37:10.561 --> 37:12.813
You don't have anything else to tell me?

37:15.816 --> 37:16.734
I do.

37:19.779 --> 37:20.613
What is it?

37:25.785 --> 37:27.203
I like you.

37:43.594 --> 37:44.428
What?

37:47.515 --> 37:48.391
What did you say?

37:48.474 --> 37:49.517
You heard me.

37:50.101 --> 37:53.229
No, I don't think so.

37:53.312 --> 37:55.481
I might have misheard you.

37:55.564 --> 37:56.941
I said

37:57.942 --> 37:59.610
I like you, Ms. Seo.

38:01.112 --> 38:04.490
What? I mean, where is this coming from?

38:07.535 --> 38:08.536
I should get going.

38:10.496 --> 38:11.330
See you tomorrow.

38:23.426 --> 38:26.053
What is he saying?

38:37.481 --> 38:38.441
Seriously.

38:39.400 --> 38:40.943
Is he actually crazy?

38:41.652 --> 38:43.654
He's messing with me, right?

38:44.864 --> 38:46.449
Wait, besides…

38:47.283 --> 38:49.076
I saw him with Eun-ju last night.

38:51.787 --> 38:52.997
That bastard!

38:53.581 --> 38:55.416
Is he trying to date two girls at work?

38:55.499 --> 38:56.751
I got rejected.

38:56.834 --> 38:59.128
At first, I was just fangirling over him.

38:59.211 --> 39:01.505
But it was late into the night,
I had a buzz going,

39:01.589 --> 39:03.966
and he was right next to me,
so I just took a shot.

39:04.050 --> 39:04.925
And?

39:05.009 --> 39:06.302
He shot me down coldly.

39:07.094 --> 39:09.013
I actually felt shot down.

39:10.389 --> 39:13.142
So, do I just need to be aware of this?

39:14.393 --> 39:15.936
Why don't you give it a thought?

39:16.020 --> 39:18.731
About dating me, that is.

39:19.315 --> 39:20.608
I don't think I can do that.

39:21.192 --> 39:22.276
Do you not like me?

39:25.196 --> 39:27.114
I don't particularly dislike you,

39:27.198 --> 39:29.200
but I don't think
I'll ever come to like you.

39:34.497 --> 39:37.583
Just a moment. Oh, my head…

39:40.419 --> 39:43.547
Wow, he really is just built differently.

39:44.048 --> 39:47.259
My phone broke, and my heart broke.
It was the worst workshop ever.

39:48.219 --> 39:49.470
What?

39:49.553 --> 39:52.515
So he actually meant what he told me?

39:56.560 --> 39:57.812
-Cover me!
-What?

39:57.895 --> 39:59.313
Why? What is it?

40:01.524 --> 40:03.609
Why?

40:03.692 --> 40:05.069
Why?

40:05.152 --> 40:07.571
Why?

40:07.655 --> 40:08.781
What are you doing?

40:10.825 --> 40:12.159
Are you playing trains?

40:12.243 --> 40:14.412
-I wanna play too!
-Off we go!

40:19.917 --> 40:21.544
Let's get back to work.

40:23.504 --> 40:24.672
I like it.

40:28.467 --> 40:30.636
The readers would really like this part.

40:30.719 --> 40:34.473
I liked the witty homage in the beginning,
and I also liked the art style.

40:34.974 --> 40:37.935
It doesn't follow the trend,
but it has a rookie's originality.

40:38.018 --> 40:41.105
In conclusion,
the readers will definitely like it.

40:41.188 --> 40:43.524
I like you.

40:44.024 --> 40:46.444
Get a grip!

40:47.069 --> 40:49.155
-Take a short break?
-Sure.

40:57.204 --> 40:58.247
Me too.

41:04.462 --> 41:05.463
Push.

41:20.102 --> 41:22.021
This is driving me crazy.

41:32.990 --> 41:34.575
We're not meeting today either?

41:36.243 --> 41:38.913
See you later. I'll leave work early.

41:52.718 --> 41:53.677
Ms. Seo.

41:53.761 --> 41:54.595
Yes?

41:55.262 --> 41:56.514
Did I make a mistake?

41:57.932 --> 41:58.766
Sorry?

42:05.648 --> 42:07.024
I didn't think you'd avoid me.

42:07.107 --> 42:10.694
Me? Avoid you? When did I ever…

42:11.529 --> 42:12.613
Can I wait

42:13.447 --> 42:14.406
for your answer?

42:15.366 --> 42:16.617
Oh God…

42:17.117 --> 42:17.952
Or

42:18.953 --> 42:19.995
should I just give up?

42:27.545 --> 42:29.547
Well, you know, I--

42:29.630 --> 42:33.008
If you're seeing someone,
you can just tell me.

42:35.344 --> 42:36.720
Well, I…

42:37.346 --> 42:38.222
I am.

42:41.433 --> 42:44.770
I am seeing someone right now.

42:45.521 --> 42:50.442
So I'll pretend
I didn't hear what you said.

42:51.694 --> 42:52.528
All right.

42:53.320 --> 42:54.154
What?

42:55.739 --> 42:56.574
I understand.

43:14.633 --> 43:18.429
Asking someone out and giving up.
Why is everything so easy for him?

43:18.512 --> 43:20.347
He's so full of himself.

43:25.519 --> 43:27.521
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM

43:28.772 --> 43:31.025
I can't tell what he's thinking.

43:31.567 --> 43:32.526
Whatever.

43:58.385 --> 44:00.471
So it's not just kumdo you're good at?

44:01.305 --> 44:02.723
I'm good at everything.

44:03.891 --> 44:04.933
Let me skate with you.

44:05.934 --> 44:06.769
Try to keep up.

44:27.247 --> 44:28.082
Eun-ho.

44:29.625 --> 44:30.793
Someone asked me out.

44:31.752 --> 44:33.712
Is it that jerk you always complain about?

44:34.421 --> 44:35.964
I knew he was going to.

44:36.965 --> 44:38.425
How did you know?

44:40.094 --> 44:41.553
I didn't see it coming at all.

44:42.429 --> 44:45.557
When I told him I had a boyfriend,
he just said, "All right."

44:45.641 --> 44:47.685
Was he trying to feel me out?

44:47.768 --> 44:50.854
Like, to see if I would fall for him?
He's so annoying.

44:50.938 --> 44:53.982
You seem distracted by some other guy
when you're with me.

44:57.361 --> 44:58.862
Are you jealous?

44:59.905 --> 45:00.823
Am not.

45:02.366 --> 45:05.119
I think you are.
You were being jealous, weren't you?

45:12.751 --> 45:14.086
Am I a little prettier?

45:14.837 --> 45:16.505
I like you.

45:24.263 --> 45:25.723
Still got it.

45:26.849 --> 45:29.601
You should try it.
I'm sure it'll look good on you.

45:32.896 --> 45:35.482
Only heartbroken people
treat themselves like that.

45:38.527 --> 45:42.239
I'm completely over it now, okay?
I'm not heartbroken.

45:42.740 --> 45:46.326
I can tell from your spending spree.
You're so not over it.

45:47.453 --> 45:49.955
I need to be prepared
for the new era, you know.

45:50.038 --> 45:53.667
It would be such a shame
to let this face of mine waste away.

45:55.252 --> 45:56.253
Whatever.

45:56.336 --> 45:57.755
Hey, it's Seo Eun-ho.

45:59.715 --> 46:00.883
What? Let me see.

46:01.717 --> 46:03.761
-He's so handsome.
-He's so handsome.

46:05.429 --> 46:07.306
-Did you try this one?
-I did this one.

46:07.389 --> 46:08.348
It's really good.

46:08.974 --> 46:10.476
-Which one?
-This one.

46:11.059 --> 46:13.312
-Did you see the Milky Way?
-Obviously.

46:14.146 --> 46:15.898
-I wanna try this one too.
-The trip?

46:16.398 --> 46:18.901
This one for me.
It starts raining all of a sudden…

46:19.818 --> 46:21.779
He's so good-looking.

46:21.862 --> 46:22.696
What is this?

46:31.538 --> 46:34.166
Seo Eun-ho, in particular,
has been receiving rave reviews.

46:34.249 --> 46:37.336
He's kind but sexy.
Strong, but you still want to protect him.

46:37.419 --> 46:39.922
I got to meet the women
who fell in love with him.

46:40.005 --> 46:41.757
K, an office worker, had this to say.

46:41.840 --> 46:43.467
Reality doesn't matter to me now.

46:43.550 --> 46:46.136
When I go on a date with him
for a few hours after work,

46:46.220 --> 46:48.472
it feels as though
I went on a date in real life.

46:48.555 --> 46:50.849
Scratch that.
It feels way better than that.

46:50.933 --> 46:53.477
College student Eun-ho's
best five moments.

46:53.560 --> 46:55.729
Five. Charismatically tying
your kumdo belt.

46:56.939 --> 46:59.691
Don't you go easy on me.
Give everything you've got.

47:01.735 --> 47:06.240
Four. Running in the sudden rain together,
like a scene out of a movie.

47:06.990 --> 47:10.244
-Three.
-To you, am I still just an upperclassman?

47:11.203 --> 47:12.120
-Two.
-The exam?

47:12.204 --> 47:14.873
The day you first confirmed
your feelings for each other.

47:14.957 --> 47:17.209
I blew it. Because of you.

47:18.293 --> 47:19.962
One. The night of the trip.

47:20.045 --> 47:23.715
The romantic moment of sitting together
and gazing at the sunset.

47:27.386 --> 47:29.304
Office worker Eun-ho's best five moments.

47:29.388 --> 47:32.307
-Five.
-Still as pretty as ever.

47:32.391 --> 47:36.645
Four. Gently tying your apron,
unlike when he was a college student.

47:36.728 --> 47:37.563
Three.

47:37.646 --> 47:40.941
I didn't know back then
that I'd never forget about you.

48:36.997 --> 48:37.831
What?

48:39.917 --> 48:41.084
Where did he go?

48:46.924 --> 48:47.758
You scared me.

48:47.841 --> 48:48.967
Surprise.

48:49.051 --> 48:50.093
Here.

48:52.346 --> 48:54.723
What's with the flowers?
Is it a special day?

48:54.806 --> 48:57.976
I just felt like
bringing you flowers today.

49:02.898 --> 49:04.066
You don't like them?

49:06.568 --> 49:08.445
I do. Thank you.

49:40.686 --> 49:41.687
What's with you today?

49:42.729 --> 49:44.731
You were quiet throughout dinner.

49:47.275 --> 49:48.402
What do you mean?

49:50.153 --> 49:51.029
Is everything okay?

49:52.823 --> 49:55.200
Yeah. Everything's fine.

50:06.044 --> 50:06.878
Mi-rae.

50:09.965 --> 50:10.799
Yes?

50:15.012 --> 50:16.013
I'm scared.

50:25.230 --> 50:26.982
That you might leave me again.

50:32.612 --> 50:34.698
Office worker Eun-ho's best five moments.

50:34.781 --> 50:35.615
Two.

50:35.699 --> 50:38.076
I'm scared. That you might leave me again.

50:38.160 --> 50:38.994
Damn it.

50:43.707 --> 50:46.126
I'm sorry. Let's talk about it next time.

51:04.895 --> 51:06.480
Did I do something wrong?

51:12.360 --> 51:13.612
It's not like that.

51:17.074 --> 51:18.241
Look at me.

51:43.058 --> 51:45.811
One. Pushing you against a wall
unexpectedly to kiss you.

51:45.894 --> 51:48.355
A sexy side hidden
beneath his gentle demeanor.

51:50.941 --> 51:54.111
This is just too much.

51:56.655 --> 51:57.656
Eun-ho.

51:59.741 --> 52:02.410
You didn't do anything wrong.

52:10.919 --> 52:12.337
I'm the one who changed.

52:14.798 --> 52:15.966
Now,

52:16.716 --> 52:19.136
no matter what killer move you pull on me,

52:19.970 --> 52:21.513
I can't get into this at all.

52:23.140 --> 52:24.349
What do you mean by that?

52:29.146 --> 52:31.606
This time, I'll tell you before I leave.

52:33.358 --> 52:34.276
Tell me what?

52:36.695 --> 52:38.655
Thank you for everything.

52:44.661 --> 52:45.871
Take care.

52:48.039 --> 52:48.874
No.

52:52.669 --> 52:55.755
You sons of bitches.
How dare you screw with me like this!

52:57.507 --> 52:59.050
Fine. I've had enough.

52:59.551 --> 53:01.178
I'm canceling my sub right away.

53:25.869 --> 53:26.703
You scared me!

53:29.080 --> 53:30.081
How have you been?

53:30.707 --> 53:31.791
Why are you here?

53:33.418 --> 53:35.086
Tell me. What's wrong?

53:39.507 --> 53:41.009
Do you not like Seo Eun-ho?

53:41.092 --> 53:43.428
Then you can just move on to the next guy.

53:45.347 --> 53:48.892
Are you here because I was about to
cancel my subscription?

53:50.310 --> 53:51.144
Oh my.

53:52.145 --> 53:53.897
What are you talking about?

53:53.980 --> 53:56.900
Goodness! No, not at all.

54:00.445 --> 54:01.988
Are you going to cancel?

54:03.990 --> 54:04.991
I don't know.

54:06.159 --> 54:10.413
Just tell me. If there's a problem,
we simply need to solve it together.

54:10.497 --> 54:14.000
Why would you jump
to such extreme measures?

54:18.672 --> 54:19.714
Tell me.

54:20.465 --> 54:23.969
How many women is Seo Eun-ho seeing?

54:27.347 --> 54:29.307
Do you really need to know that?

54:30.392 --> 54:33.395
Yes. I really need to know.

54:34.854 --> 54:35.689
All right.

54:36.940 --> 54:37.941
Here.

54:40.026 --> 54:40.860
CHOI SI-WOO

54:40.944 --> 54:41.778
SEO EUN-HO

54:43.738 --> 54:46.157
12,432 people.

54:46.658 --> 54:47.492
What?

54:47.575 --> 54:49.411
Now it's 12,434.

54:49.494 --> 54:52.747
Twelve thousand…

54:52.831 --> 54:54.666
Why did you have to ask?

54:54.749 --> 54:58.545
That means he did and said the same things
to other women too.

54:58.628 --> 55:00.755
And there are what, twelve thousand and…

55:01.715 --> 55:02.549
What is it?

55:03.341 --> 55:05.218
What? Did it just go up again?

55:06.636 --> 55:09.055
Now it's 12,45…

55:09.806 --> 55:11.558
I'm good now. Stop.

55:13.310 --> 55:14.436
So are you saying

55:14.519 --> 55:18.523
you don't like the fact that Seo Eun-ho
is available to other women as well?

55:19.733 --> 55:21.026
Yes.

55:21.109 --> 55:22.027
I mean…

55:22.110 --> 55:24.446
My head gets it, but my heart…

55:25.822 --> 55:29.367
But it can't be helped.
And if you think about it, it's natural.

55:29.451 --> 55:31.745
It's not like this is an issue
that can be solved.

55:33.621 --> 55:34.664
There is a solution.

55:37.292 --> 55:38.168
What?

55:38.251 --> 55:39.711
It can be solved.

55:39.794 --> 55:42.130
I can match you up with a guy
only available to you.

55:42.213 --> 55:44.341
As if that kind of guy even exists.

55:45.050 --> 55:47.886
The number of men in Boyfriend on Demand

55:47.969 --> 55:50.972
isn't 900 but 901, to be exact.

55:51.598 --> 55:56.728
I'm saying we can generate
one custom-tailored boyfriend per account.

56:00.106 --> 56:04.319
What do you mean by "custom-tailored"?

56:06.237 --> 56:11.451
We'll generate a boyfriend
perfectly tailored for you and you alone.

56:11.534 --> 56:13.161
Gu Yeong-il.

56:17.290 --> 56:18.708
Gu Yeong-il?

56:26.383 --> 56:27.384
Ms. Seo Mi-rae,

56:27.467 --> 56:31.638
please take the survey to create
a custom-tailored boyfriend on BoD.

56:32.138 --> 56:35.475
To do that,
we need to know you in more detail.

56:35.558 --> 56:38.812
What kind of looks you like,
what kind of personality you like.

56:38.895 --> 56:42.982
Whether you want to take the lead
or be led. We'll analyze everything.

56:45.276 --> 56:46.277
Let's see.

56:46.361 --> 56:49.614
"I like the uncomfortable feeling
of dating a heartthrob."

56:50.156 --> 56:51.032
No.

56:51.116 --> 56:54.411
"I prefer a man who's sexy at times
over a man who's sexy all the time."

56:55.787 --> 56:58.915
"I'm attracted to men who show it
instead of saying it." Definitely.

57:04.838 --> 57:06.589
There are so many of them.

57:07.507 --> 57:08.925
Just how many are there?

57:10.510 --> 57:14.472
"Please describe your ideal man in detail,
within 2,000 characters"?

57:16.015 --> 57:17.225
Seriously?

57:18.810 --> 57:20.437
Why are there so many?

57:25.066 --> 57:26.067
How good is it anyway?

57:26.151 --> 57:29.946
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND 901

57:30.029 --> 57:31.865
Gu Yeong-il is the champion of BoD.

57:31.948 --> 57:33.366
I'm so proud of my fine taste!

57:33.450 --> 57:36.369
Helped me get through the worst breakup.
A true lifesaver.

57:36.453 --> 57:38.163
901 taught love to a lifelong single.

57:38.246 --> 57:40.748
Gu Yeong-il alone is enough
to make me subscribe.

57:40.832 --> 57:43.460
The man I didn't know I wanted.
He amazes me every day.

57:52.385 --> 57:54.596
Optimization complete.

57:56.055 --> 57:57.974
I don't know where I'm headed,

57:58.475 --> 58:03.605
but waiting at the end of this road
is someone who's a perfect match for me.

59:01.746 --> 59:02.664
What the heck?

59:59.262 --> 01:00:00.847
Doors opening.

01:00:01.347 --> 01:00:02.181
Hello.

01:00:08.646 --> 01:00:10.106
Doors closing.

01:01:13.836 --> 01:01:15.254
What are you looking for?

01:01:15.338 --> 01:01:16.756
God, you scared me.

01:01:19.676 --> 01:01:22.345
No, I just…

01:01:27.266 --> 01:01:28.101
Ta-da!

01:01:29.352 --> 01:01:30.353
It's this, right?

01:01:39.696 --> 01:01:40.571
There we go.

01:03:46.739 --> 01:03:51.744
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon
